# UI Design Standards — BOLOOT Persian Calendar (boloot.ir)

## GNOME HIG + libadwaita (settings)
- Use `Adw.PreferencesWindow`, `Adw.PreferencesPage`, `Adw.ActionRow`, `Adw.SwitchRow`, `Adw.ComboRow`.
- Prefer `Adw.ColorRow` over raw hex `Gtk.Entry` for colors.
- Show live preview after save; use `Adw.Toast` for confirmation.
- Default `use_system_theme: true`; custom colors only when user opts out.

## Semantic colors (map to libadwaita when themed)
- `holiday_color` → `@destructive_color`
- `today_color` → `@accent_color`
- `prayer_color` → `@success_color`
- `text_color` → `@window_fg_color`

## GNOME Shell extension
- Use `PanelMenu.Button` + `PopupMenu` on click (calendar, holidays, prayer).
- Sync settings via D-Bus `GetSettings` / `SettingsChanged`; do not duplicate config state.
- Refresh: 60s for date; 1s only when countdown prayer mode is active.
- Provide accessible names; support `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## RTL & Persian
- Settings: `set_default_direction(RTL)` for fa/fa_AF locales.
- Use logical CSS properties (`margin-start`, not `margin-left`).
- i18n via gettext (`fa`, `fa_AF`, `ps`, `tg`); display strings from `core` only.

## Accessibility
- WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 text, 3:1 large text).
- Keyboard navigation in settings; touch targets ≥ 44px in popup.

## Top bar UX
- Compact format in panel; full detail in popup only.
- Truncate with ellipsis when space is limited; separator ` · ` between date and prayer.
